<p>I&rsquo;m a television news journalist living in London. This blog is for making sure I don&rsquo;t forget how to write sentences. It&rsquo;s probably best to think of it as three individual microsites:</p>

<h1 id="politicstagpolitics"><a href="http://127.0.0.1:2368/tag/politics">Politics</a></h1>

<p>My thoughts on the issues being raised by the British media and beyond.</p>

<h1 id="startupstagstartups"><a href="tag/startups">Startups</a></h1>

<p>In my spare time, I love to try out business ideas. My main project at the moment is <a href="http://www.getshopaholic.com">Shopaholic</a>, a Google Chrome plugin which lets you follow your favourite clothes shops and turns your new tab page into a feed of sale items from them. Geared towards people like me who aren&rsquo;t working on their startups full time, I&rsquo;ll be sharing what I learn from my ventures, from marketing tips to handy code snippets.</p>

<h1 id="musictagmusic"><a href="tag/music">Music</a></h1>

<p>Classical music has been a passion for as long as I can remember. Since my first violin lessons at an early age, I&rsquo;ve never stopped discovering new artists and composers. (In fact, I spent my first year at Cambridge reading music before switching to law &mdash; long story.) On here, I&rsquo;ll share my latest obsessions as and when I discover them.</p>

<h1 id="lifestyletaglifestyle"><a href="http://127.0.0.1:2368/tag/lifestyle">Lifestyle</a></h1>

<p>Beside the occasional self-indulgent account of days out or trips abroad, expect to  alongside other cool things worth sharing.</p>

<p><em>My old website can still be viewed <a href="http://old.sebastiansalek.com">here</a>.</em></p>
            </section>


